-- King Says There Are Signs of Recovery in U.K. Economy
-- B y   A n d r e w   A t k i n s o n
-- 2013-06-02T10:26:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-02/king-says-there-are-signs-of-recovery-in-u-k-economy.html
Bank of England  Governor Mervyn King
said there are signs the U.K. economy is recovering, though
output is not expanding “as fast as we’d like it to grow.”  King made his comments in an interview for BBC Radio 4’s
“Desert Island Discs” show broadcast today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Atkinson in London at 
